facts_and_links: {'Trivia': ["The title Love in Bright Landscapes is taken from a Triffids compilation of the same name, released in 1986. David McComb took it from a poem published by Spanish poet Rafael Albert in 1974, called 'The Coming Back of Love in Bright Landscapes'. The poem has the alternate title of 'The Coming Back of Love on the Sands' , and it was once transcribed by McComb using this title.", 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt15018726/trivia/?ref_=tt_dyk_trv']}

movie_name: Dear Ike: Lost Letters to a Teen Idol
short_description: In this animated documentary, Los Angeles filmmaker Dion Labriola recounts his all-consuming childhood quest to contact his teen idol, Ike Eisenmann - and the magical turn of events that led him toward his goal (some 40 years later).
